@unepic_fran does it again! This is a fantastic game. It has some really clever procedual arena combat systems built into the metroidvania shell. 
Basicly- Spaced around the map are these alarm triggered security stations. Usually you can walk right by them but some you have to trigger to progress. They lock you in the room and send out a flood of randomly placed enemies for you to fight. Once you clear the areana you can get a new weapon or a power up. Clearing several areans will make you stronger and help you out in other areas of the game, however every time you beat an arena the alarm system goes up a level and the next area will be harder. If you die you lose ALL of your power ups and start from your last save point with all your progress intact. 
This dynamic difficulty means as you grow more powerful the game also gets harder, and you can challenge yourself to clear as many security stations as possible.

